\\subsection\{Quotes and block quotes\}\par
\par
\\begin\{itemize\}\par
\\item\par
Use double quotes. Do not use single quotes, except for ``quotes `within' quotes''.\par
\\item\par
Use the following style for block quotes. Do not use quote marks.\par
\\end\{itemize\}\par
\par
\\begin\{quote\}\par
Use for quotes that are more than about four lines in length. Indent from both\par
margins. For direct quotes reproduce the exact spelling and punctuation of the\par
original. Any interpolations should be enclosed in square brackets. Do not forget to\par
acknowledge the source of your quote and seek permission if necessary.\par
(See Permissions.)\par
\\end\{quote\}\par
\par
This is produced by\par
\\begin\{verbatim\}\par
\\begin\{quote\}\par
...\par
\\end\{quote\}\par
\\end\{verbatim\}\par
The quote is set in the same font size as the rest of the text and one line\par
of space is left above and below.\par
\par
\par
\\subsection\{Cross-referencing\}\par
\par
The use of the \\LaTeX\\ cross-reference system for figures, tables, equations,\par
etc., is encouraged (using \\verb"\\ref\{<name>\}" and \\verb"\\label\{<name>\}").\par
\par
\par
\\subsection\{Acknowledgements\}\par
\par
An acknowledgements section is started with \\verb"\\ack" or \\verb"\\acks"\par
for \\textit\{Acknowledgement\} or \\textit\{Acknowledgements\}, respectively. It\par
must be placed just before the references (or before the appendix when applicable).\par
\par
\par
\\subsection\{Bibliography\}\par
\par
The package \\textsf\{natbib\} is loaded by \\textsf\{oupau.cls\} and can be\par
used to achieve either of the following reference citations. Further details\par
can be found in the notes accompanying the \\textsf\{natbib\} package.\par
\par
\\subsubsection\{Numbered references\}\par
\par
The commands for producing the reference list are:\par
\\begin\{verbatim\}\par
\\begin\{thebibliography\}\{00\}\par
\\bibitem\{<bibid1>\} <Reference details>\par
.\par
.\par
.\par
\\bibitem\{<bibid20>\} <Reference details>\par
\\end\{thebibliography\}\par
\\end\{verbatim\}\par
and the first reference above can be referred to in the text using\par
\\verb"\\cite\{<bibid1>\}".\par
\par
This is a citation of reference \\cite\{Abe:2008\} in the text and the\par
following commands form part of the output that occurs at the end of this document:\par
\\begin\{verbatim\}\par
\\begin\{thebibliography\}\{0\}\par
\\bibitem\{Abe:2008\}\par
Abe, T.\par
``Degeneration of the strange duality map for symplectic bundles.''\par
\\textit\{Journal of Mathematics\} 56, no. 5 (2008): 5--10.\par
\\end\{thebibliography\}\par
\\end\{verbatim\}\par
\par
\\subsubsection\{Name/date references\}\par
\par
The commands for producing the reference list are:\par
\\begin\{verbatim\}\par
\\begin\{thebibliography\}\{0\}\par
\\bibitem[\\protect\\citeauthoryear\{<complete author list>\}\par
\{<first author et al.>\}\{<year>\}]\{<bibid1>\}\par
<Reference details>\par
.\par
.\par
.\par
\\bibitem[\\protect\\citeauthoryear\{<complete author list>\}\par
\{<first author et al.>\}\{<year>\}]\{<bibid20>\}\par
<Reference details>\par
\\end\{thebibliography\}\par
\\end\{verbatim\}\par
and these reference can be referred to in the text using\par
\\verb"\\cite\{<bibid1>\}", \\verb"\\citet\{<bibid20>\}", etc.\par
